r brooks also serves as a member of the board of directors of energy xxi  scott heck chief operating officer mr scott m heck is chief operating officer for energy xxi gulf coast inc scott joined energy xxi in february of   scott has worked in ep for over  years and recently served as chief operating officer for bennu oil  gas llc overseeing all exploration and production operations reporting to bennu’s chief executive officer he retired from hess corporation in early  where he was senior vice president of global offshore production  global exploration in this capacity he was responsible for the operations and development of assets producing in excess of  boepd from eight countries around the world including a prominent position in the gulf of mexico his responsibilities also included leading the organization responsible for capturing maturing and discovering conventional exploration opportunities in the gulf of mexico west africa  south america conjugate margin and malaysia prior to his most recent hess role he served as senior vice president of exploration  production technology which he established then subsequently led to provide support to solve critical technical challenges faced by the company’s global ep business this role was also responsible for the company’s global reserves group and included assuring compliance with sec rules and spe prms guidelines earlier in his tenure at hess scott served in a variety of technical and leadership roles including manager  gom offshore engineering manager  gom offshore production  development vice president – west africa production and senior vice president  americas  west africa production  he began his career with tenneco oil in bakersfield california in  and holds a bachelor’s degree in petroleum engineering from marietta college  hugh menown executive vice president interim chief financial officer and chief accounting officer mr menown has served as executive vice president interim chief financial officer and chief accounting officer of energy xxi since february  and as executive vice president chief accounting officer of energy xxi since may  previously he served as chief information officer of energy xxi from july  to october  and he served as senior vice president from july  until june  when he was promoted to executive vice president from august  until his appointment as our chief accounting officer mr menown worked for energy xxi as an independent consultant working for the first seven months of  as an independent consultant in the energy industry from march  until december  mr menown was employed by quanta services inc serving as chief financial officer of two of its subsidiaries from  to  mr menown provided audit and related services for clients at pricewaterhousecoopers llp in the houston office where for seven years he was the partner in charge of the transaction services practice providing due diligence mergers and acquisition advisory and strategic consulting to numerous clients in various industries mr menown has more than  years of experience in mergers and acquisitions auditing and managerial finance is a certified public accountant and a  graduate of the university of missouricolumbia with a bachelor’s degree in business administration kerry mcdonough senior vice president human resources and administration interim corporate secretary kerry mcdonough joined energy xxi in  and serves as the company’s senior vice president of human resources and administration  since february  ms mcdonough also serves as interim corporate secretary  prior to energy xxi ms mcdonough held various human resources positions with increasing responsibility working for large organizations such as md anderson cancer center occidental oil  gas calpine corporation and burlington resources  ms mcdonough has more than  years of human resources experience in areas including organizational development change management employee relations and diversity ms mcdonough holds a bachelor of business adm